03/11/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The High Court of Justice on Monday (November 2nd) stripped a judge from Elbasan, accused of corruption, of his immunity.
Judge Qani Hasa was investigated after prosecutors received a tip from a whistle blower.
Separately Monday, the High Court of Justice signed an agreement with the Justice Ministry to intensify control over local courts.
All decisions related to murder and corruption taken by the courts over the last two years will be "scanned" by the High Court of Justice.
(Shekulli, Top Channel - 02/11/09
